Roslyn has 20 boxes in total, where:- 13 boxes contain pencils- 9 boxes contain pens- 3 boxes contain neither pens nor pencilsThe problem is to find the number of boxes that contain both pens and pencils.The diagram representing the problem can be drawn using LaTeX as follows: egin{center} egin{tikzpicture}\draw (0,0) circle (2cm) node [above] {Pencils};\draw (3,0) circle (2cm) node [above] {Pens};
ode at (1.5,0) {$x$};
ode at (0.5,1) {$13-x$};
ode at (2.5,1) {$9-x$};\end{tikzpicture}\end{center}

A domino is made up of two congruent squares placed side by side. The perimeter of the domino is given as 60 units. The task is to find the area of the domino in square units.Let's represent the domino using LaTeX: egin{tikzpicture}\draw (0,0) rectangle (2,1);\draw (2,0) rectangle (4,1);
ode at (1,0.5) {$l$};
ode at (3,0.5) {$l$};
ode at (1,1.2) {$l$};
ode at (3,1.2) {$l$};
ode at (2,0.5) {$l$};\end{tikzpicture}Where $l$ represents the length of the shorter side of the domino.
